12-3-1. General qualifications of voters.

An individual may vote at an election in this state only if, at the time of the election, the individual:

(1)Is a citizen of the United States;

(2)Maintains residence in this state, as defined in §12-1-4;

(3)Is at least eighteen years of age;

(4)Is not otherwise disqualified; and

(5)Complies with the law regarding the registration of voters, pursuant to chapter 12-4.

Source: PolC 1877, ch 27, §47; CL 1887, §1486; RPolC 1903, §1866; RC 1919, §7213; SDC 1939, §16.0604; SL 1972, ch 76, §1; SL 1973, ch 69, §2; SL 2023, ch 42, §2; SL 2025, ch 59, §1.
